					<description><![CDATA[ATFX continues its partnership with the Duke of Edinburgh Cup, the charity belonging to the British Royal Family, dedicated to helping young people worldwide by providing and giving support in health, education and welfare. On October 21, 2023, the highly anticipated Duke of Edinburgh Cup Turkey Qualifiers took place at the Gloria Golf Club Belek, [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>ATFX continues its partnership with the <a href="https://www.atfx.com/en/duke-of-edinburgh-cup-sponsorship" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Duke of Edinburgh Cup</a>, the charity belonging to the British Royal Family, dedicated to helping young people worldwide by providing and giving support in health, education and welfare.</p>
<p>On October 21, 2023, the highly anticipated <strong>Duke of Edinburgh Cup Turkey Qualifiers</strong> took place at the <em>Gloria Golf Club Belek, Antalya</em>. As the official partner of the event, Joe Li, Chairman of ATFX and Wei Qiang Zhang, Managing Director of ATFX UK, attended the event. On the eve of the event, we also had the opportunity to meet local important guests from various backgrounds through a welcome reception, adding value to our brand&#8217;s expansion efforts. During the event, Joe Li, Chairman of ATFX, delivered an important speech.</p>
<p><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" class="aligncenter  wp-image-26593" src="https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/b6579651-3388-4667-8084-8d42f976d3b8.webp" alt="ATFX Official Partner Duke of Edinburgh Cup Turkey" width="1029" height="686" srcset="https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/b6579651-3388-4667-8084-8d42f976d3b8.webp 1178w, https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/b6579651-3388-4667-8084-8d42f976d3b8-300x200.webp 300w, https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/b6579651-3388-4667-8084-8d42f976d3b8-1024x682.webp 1024w, https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/b6579651-3388-4667-8084-8d42f976d3b8-768x512.webp 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1029px) 100vw, 1029px" /></p>
<p>During the competition, ATFX provides participants with the necessary equipment for the event and establishes significant connections with players, distinguished guests, and others through offline communication. ATFX and the guests have the opportunity to delve into various cultural traditions and cultivate amicable relationships.</p>
<p>In February 2023, Turkey experienced its most powerful earthquake in 70 years. All funds raised during this tournament were used to support children and young people affected by the earthquake in Turkey. ATFX has continued supporting young children worldwide through the Duke of Edinburgh Golf Cup for five consecutive years in three different continents and is committed to continue supporting local communities in the coming years.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
